<br>
At 25 my best heal is greater heal. about 300 hp healing. Most tanks around my level thats just over 2 bubs, If I throw it on them before that point im taking aggro so thats a no no.<br>
<br>
Casters, alot of them at my level still have a tencency to over nuke and get aggroed. In that light I have to keep stun, holy might, and sometimes root memmed so I can help save them. Doing that though forces aggro on me. alas the perils of a cleric.<br>
<br>
multiple pulls, this is a toughie. If all melees know how, and use assist, then the only thing you have to worry about is making sure you dont wait too long on the main assist. If, however, your melees dont know how to use assist and you cant get them to understand the concept of assist, your job just got ten times harder. You will find yourself medding desperately to get enough mana for one heal. If you find yourself above 20% mana in this situation consider yourself lucky. <br>
<br>
inconsiderate tanks, the bane of all groups. I find this one easy to handle. just dont heal them. If you have backups in your group, tell them not to heal them also. They will either die, learn quickly when you are ready for them to pull, or both. Hopefully no hard feelings come with the latter.<br>
<br>
working with other healers, this can be such a pleasure IF you are working with patient and cooperative people. While they alternate between nukes and heals, you can sit back and monitor the battle, call adds if need be, take care of the emergency big heals, keep more than half mana, occasionally melee (not recommended against red mobs), and even nuke(be mana efficient with this). <br>
<br>
caster mobs, oh how i hate them. I would like to be able to tell all party members to destroy these things first, fast, and foremost. That cant happen all the time though so I have to depend on the nukers in the group, which leads us to the problem of overnuking. see above.<br>
<br>
So many strategies that the only thing I can tell you is you learn as you go, and you also learn to be the second most flexible class out there.<br>
<br>
